{[#]} 10. Kh1 $1 {[%cal Gg2g3] It's a good idea to do something about the
opponent's most active piece. This way, we prepare to push it out with g2-g3.}
Nf6 11. g3 Nh3 12. Nh4 $14 {[%cal Gf2f3,Gh4g2,Gc1e3,Yc4c5,Yf3f4,Rf7f5] White
has the f5-break under control. Moreover, he can strengthen his position with
normal developing moves and gradually prepare his queenside play or the
f4-break, depending on the circumstances.} *

